mplate literals I've ever seen -- so slick and clean :+1:), I found some more constraints on using that workaround:\r\n\r\nIf a color block precedes it, it works:\r\n```js\r\n> console.log(chalk`testing {blue hi}${'\\n'}there`)\r\ntesting hi\r\nthere\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf a color block follows it, it eats the `\\n`:\r\n```js\r\n> console.log(chalk`testing hi${'\\n'}{blue there}`)\r\ntesting hithere\r\n```\r\n\r\nProbably doesn't matter if you know how you think you'd like to change it; but, I thought I'd mention it anyway.\r\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/chalk/chalk/issues/comments/316553329/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"cognisent","id":1672405,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2NzI0MDU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1672405?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent","html_url":"https://github.com/cognisent","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cognisent/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/chalk/chalk/issues/comments/316834933","html_url":"https://github.com/chalk/chalk/issues/177#issuecomment-316834933","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/chalk/chalk/issues/177","id":316834933,"no